<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="252" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,541,1646]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,685,710]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yosii, R." box="[324,466,685,710]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" pagination="1 - 109" refId="ref5651" refString="Yosii, R. (1956) Monographie zur Hohlencollembolen Japans. Contributions from the Biological Laboratory Kyoto University, 3, 1 - 109." type="journal article" year="1956">Yosii (1956)</bibRefCitation>
described this species on material from central 
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1087,686,709]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Later he (
<bibRefCitation author="Yoshii, R." box="[1211,1352,685,710]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" pagination="3 - 10" refId="ref5677" refString="Yoshii, R. (1991) About the prozerpinae group of Hypogastrura (Collembola) in the Caves of Pref. Iwate. Annals of the Speleological Research Institute of Japan, Iwaizumi, 9, 3 - 10." type="journal article" year="1991">Yoshii 1991</bibRefCitation>
) added further details based on specimens from several caves located in 
<collectingRegion box="[907,1097,721,746]" country="Japan" name="Iwate" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Iwate Prefecture</collectingRegion>
, in the more northern part of Honshu Island. Both descriptions are not complete and partly contradict each other. More detailed description of chaetotaxy is given in his 1991 paper as follows: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
chaetal pattern is strongly variable, namely, on abd. I–III, s.s. is p-5, the setae m-1, m-3 and m- 
<date box="[492,559,830,854]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">4 may</date>
be present or absent, on abd. IV s.s. is p-4 and m-1 is often on one side and m- 3, m-4 are usually present.
</emphasis>
Such a description indicates a high level of variability but does not allow an exact interpretation of the pattern of chaetotaxy. Description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yosii" authorityYear="1956" box="[814,1019,901,926]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinqueoculata">
<emphasis box="[814,1019,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. quinqueoculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
chaetom by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jordana, R. &amp; Baquero, E. &amp; Reboleira, S. &amp; Sendra, A." box="[1170,1408,901,926]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" pagination="35 - 85" refId="ref5308" refString="Jordana, R., Baquero, E., Reboleira, S. &amp; Sendra, A. (2012) Reviews of the genera Schaefferia Absolon, 1900, Deuteraphorura Absolon, 1901, Plutomurus Yosii, 1956 and the Anurida Laboulbene, 1865 species group without eyes, with the description of four new species of cave springtails (Collembola) from Krubera-Voronya cave, Arabika Massif, Abkhazia. Terrestrial Arthropods Reviews, 5, 35 - 85. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187498312 X 622430" type="journal article" year="2012">
Jordana 
<emphasis box="[1266,1317,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
is simply based on that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Thibaud, J. - M. &amp; Schulz, H. - J. &amp; Gama Assalino, M. M. da" box="[433,679,937,962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" pagination="1 - 287" refId="ref5511" refString="Thibaud, J. - M., Schulz, H. - J. &amp; Gama Assalino, M. M. da (2004) Hypogastruridae. In: Dunger, W. (Ed.), Synopses on Palaearctic Collembola. Vol. 4. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Naturkundemuseums Gorlitz, 75 (2), 1 - 287." type="journal article" year="2004">
Thibaud 
<emphasis box="[536,587,937,962]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">et al</emphasis>
. (2004)
</bibRefCitation>
who used a broad conception for this species. Yosii’s 
<typeStatus box="[1313,1372,938,962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yosii" authorityYear="1956" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinqueoculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. quinqueoculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could not be found. There is no such material in Museum of Natural History of Geneva where the main part of the Yosii’s collection is kept (Peter J. Schwendinger, pers. comm.), nor in the sorted collection of 
<collectingRegion box="[151,221,1046,1070]" country="Japan" name="Kyoto" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Kyoto</collectingRegion>
University Museum (M. Hasegawa, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,541,1646]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
Taizo Nakamori (Yokohama National University) collected fresh material of a similar non-cave form from central 
<collectingCountry box="[236,303,1118,1141]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Japan</collectingCountry>
. As true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yosii" authorityYear="1956" box="[407,610,1117,1142]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinqueoculata">
<emphasis box="[407,610,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. quinqueoculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is characterised by the presence of only traces of dark pigment (only eye field clearly darker), usual 7 blunt sensilla on 
<emphasis box="[734,773,1154,1177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Ant</emphasis>
.4, 5+5 ocelli (one specimen with 5+6), typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kottelat" authorityYear="2013" box="[1325,1372,1154,1177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tetraodontidae" genus="Pao" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1325,1372,1154,1177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">PAO</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 4+4 chaetae on 
<emphasis box="[276,307,1190,1213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">VT</emphasis>
, unguis with inner and a pair of lateral teeth, retinaculum with 4+4 teeth, short furca with 5(6) dental chaetae and clearly separate mucro. Its labium is complete with all usual papilla (
<figureCitation box="[1079,1148,1225,1250]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[225,1367,238,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[184,1411,195,1930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Schaefferia bermani sp. nov. (1–2, 5–8), S. czernovi (3) and S. cf. quinqueoculata (4): 1, dorsal chaetotaxy; 2, labial palp; 2a, labial papilla E, lateral view; 3, labial palp; 4, ibid; 5, maxillary head; 6–7, dens and mucro, different views; 8, unguis. Scales: Figs 1—0.1 mm, 2–8—0.01 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608298/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) which distinguishes this form from 
<taxonomicName box="[276,400,1262,1285]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernovi">
<emphasis box="[276,400,1262,1285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. czernovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The dorsal chaetae are long, thin and usually smooth (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1115,1261,1286]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[188,1412,1182,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1086,1980]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. Abdominal chaetotaxy: 9, Schaefferia czernovi; 10, quinqueoculata. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608300/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
), their distribution is almost stable and only few asymmetries were observed in the material examined. General chaetotaxic pattern is of the typical 
<emphasis box="[234,251,1334,1357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">A</emphasis>
- 
<typeStatus box="[259,312,1334,1358]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">type</typeStatus>
; that is the head and thorax with all usual chaetae present and abdomen as in 
<figureCitation box="[1186,1268,1333,1358]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[188,1412,1182,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1086,1980]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. Abdominal chaetotaxy: 9, Schaefferia czernovi; 10, quinqueoculata. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608300/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
. Using the key in Jordana 
<emphasis box="[276,327,1369,1394]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">et al</emphasis>
. (2004) the specimens are identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[781,906,1370,1393]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernovi">
<emphasis box="[781,906,1370,1393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. czernovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but not as 
<emphasis box="[1040,1252,1369,1394]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yosii" authorityYear="1956" box="[1040,1248,1369,1394]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinqueoculata">S. quinqueoculata</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The only sound difference in chaetotaxy of this form is the presence of 
<emphasis box="[782,796,1406,1429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">a</emphasis>
2’ chaetae on 
<emphasis box="[956,1001,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Abd</emphasis>
.5, i.e. 4+4 
<emphasis box="[1132,1146,1406,1429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">a</emphasis>
-chaetae situated between macrochaetae 
<emphasis box="[314,328,1442,1465]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">p</emphasis>
5 (
<figureCitation box="[360,446,1441,1466]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[188,1412,1182,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1086,1980]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. Abdominal chaetotaxy: 9, Schaefferia czernovi; 10, quinqueoculata. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608300/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). The only other described congener with such trait is 
<taxonomicName authority="Dallai et Sabatini, 1981" authorityName="Dallai et Sabatini" authorityYear="1981" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scossiroli">
<emphasis box="[1082,1219,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. scossiroli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dallai, R. &amp; Sabatini, M. A." pageId="5" pageNumber="252" pagination="195 - 204" refId="ref5084" refString="Dallai, R. &amp; Sabatini, M. A. (1981) Ricerche sui Collemboli. XXVIII Su di una nuova specie endogea di Schaefferia. Redia, 64, 195 - 204." type="journal article" year="1981">Dallai et Sabatini, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[279,330,1477,1502]" name="Italy" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Italy</collectingCountry>
but it has only 3+3 ocelli. It is not possible to definitively decide if the form described above is conspecific with true cave 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yosii" authorityYear="1956" box="[460,665,1513,1538]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinqueoculata">
<emphasis box="[460,665,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. quinqueoculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
although it is plausible. If so, a higher variability of the species in caves can be explained by long period of isolation. A new collection of this species from the type-locality is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="253" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,541,1646]" box="[199,423,1621,1646]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1621,1646]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,423,1622,1645]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Japan</collectingCountry>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1693,2006]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,320]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="253" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1693,1718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Conclusion</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Christiansen, K. &amp; Wang, H." box="[347,741,1693,1718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" pagination="82 - 95" refId="ref5039" refString="Christiansen, K. &amp; Wang, H. (2006) A revision of the genus Typhlogastrura in North American caves with description of five new species. Journal of Cave and Karst Studies, 68 (2), 82 - 95." type="journal article" year="2006">Christiansen &amp; Wang (2006, p. 82)</bibRefCitation>
noted that 
<taxonomicName authority="Bonet, 1930" authorityName="Bonet" authorityYear="1930" box="[867,1184,1693,1718]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Typhlogastrura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[867,1039,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Typhlogastrura</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bonet, F." box="[1047,1184,1694,1718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" pagination="113 - 139" refId="ref4902" refString="Bonet, F. (1930) Remarques sur les Hypogastruriens cavernicoles avec descriptions d'especes nouvelles (Collembola). EOS, Revista Espanola de Entomologia, 6 (2), 113 - 139." type="journal article" year="1930">Bonet, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">an artificial genus consisting of all members of the denticulata branch of Ceratophysella, which have successfully invaded caves and become troglomorphic</emphasis>
”. The same seems to be true for the genus 
<emphasis box="[886,1021,1765,1790]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Absolon" authorityYear="1900" box="[886,1017,1765,1790]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Schaefferia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The species of the latter genus dwell in both edaphic and cave habitats and include 
<emphasis box="[674,845,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Ceratophysella</emphasis>
species of the same branch with reduced number of eyes and shortened furca, which may not be closely related to each other. The genus is not especially diverse on the global scale and includes according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellinger, P. F. &amp; Christiansen, K. A. &amp; Janssens, F." box="[589,839,1873,1898]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" refId="ref4809" refString="Bellinger, P. F., Christiansen, K. A. &amp; Janssens, F. (2018) Checklist of the Collembola of the World. Available from: http: // www. collembola. org (accessed 29 January 2019)" type="url" year="2018">
Bellinger 
<emphasis box="[700,757,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
only 34 species. Nevertheless, two general revisions have been devoted to it during the last fifteen years, i.e. 
<bibRefCitation author="Thibaud, J. - M. &amp; Schulz, H. - J. &amp; Gama Assalino, M. M. da" box="[782,1020,1909,1934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" pagination="1 - 287" refId="ref5511" refString="Thibaud, J. - M., Schulz, H. - J. &amp; Gama Assalino, M. M. da (2004) Hypogastruridae. In: Dunger, W. (Ed.), Synopses on Palaearctic Collembola. Vol. 4. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Naturkundemuseums Gorlitz, 75 (2), 1 - 287." type="journal article" year="2004">
Thibaud 
<emphasis box="[882,939,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">et al.</emphasis>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Jordana, R. &amp; Baquero, E. &amp; Reboleira, S. &amp; Sendra, A." box="[1075,1311,1909,1934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" pagination="35 - 85" refId="ref5308" refString="Jordana, R., Baquero, E., Reboleira, S. &amp; Sendra, A. (2012) Reviews of the genera Schaefferia Absolon, 1900, Deuteraphorura Absolon, 1901, Plutomurus Yosii, 1956 and the Anurida Laboulbene, 1865 species group without eyes, with the description of four new species of cave springtails (Collembola) from Krubera-Voronya cave, Arabika Massif, Abkhazia. Terrestrial Arthropods Reviews, 5, 35 - 85. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187498312 X 622430" type="journal article" year="2012">
Jordana 
<emphasis box="[1169,1226,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
. Neither of these revisions is able to separate 
<taxonomicName authority="Babenko, 2019" authorityName="Babenko" authorityYear="2019" box="[537,659,1945,1970]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bermani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[537,659,1945,1970]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. bermani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[668,766,1945,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[668,760,1945,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[774,898,1946,1969]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernovi">
<emphasis box="[774,898,1946,1969]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. czernovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yosii" authorityYear="1956" box="[955,1158,1945,1970]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinqueoculata">
<emphasis box="[955,1158,1945,1970]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. quinqueoculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For instance, following 
<bibRefCitation author="Thibaud, J. - M. &amp; Schulz, H. - J. &amp; Gama Assalino, M. M. da" box="[151,408,1981,2006]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" pagination="1 - 287" refId="ref5511" refString="Thibaud, J. - M., Schulz, H. - J. &amp; Gama Assalino, M. M. da (2004) Hypogastruridae. In: Dunger, W. (Ed.), Synopses on Palaearctic Collembola. Vol. 4. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Naturkundemuseums Gorlitz, 75 (2), 1 - 287." type="journal article" year="2004">
Thibaud 
<emphasis box="[257,319,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">et al.</emphasis>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
, would result in the three species being identified as synonyms of 
<emphasis box="[1221,1437,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yosii" authorityYear="1956" box="[1221,1433,1981,2006]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinqueoculata">S. quinqueoculata</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Alternatively, using the key in 
<bibRefCitation author="Jordana, R. &amp; Baquero, E. &amp; Reboleira, S. &amp; Sendra, A." box="[506,746,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" pagination="35 - 85" refId="ref5308" refString="Jordana, R., Baquero, E., Reboleira, S. &amp; Sendra, A. (2012) Reviews of the genera Schaefferia Absolon, 1900, Deuteraphorura Absolon, 1901, Plutomurus Yosii, 1956 and the Anurida Laboulbene, 1865 species group without eyes, with the description of four new species of cave springtails (Collembola) from Krubera-Voronya cave, Arabika Massif, Abkhazia. Terrestrial Arthropods Reviews, 5, 35 - 85. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187498312 X 622430" type="journal article" year="2012">
Jordana 
<emphasis box="[602,660,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Babenko, 2019" authorityName="Babenko" authorityYear="2019" box="[759,882,151,176]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bermani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[759,882,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">S. bermani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[892,983,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[892,983,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
would be identified as the European 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deharveng et Thibaud" authorityYear="1980" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">S. maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while both 
<taxonomicName box="[384,508,189,212]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernovi">
<emphasis box="[384,508,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">S. czernovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(partly) and 
<emphasis box="[657,671,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">S</emphasis>
. cf. 
<emphasis box="[724,884,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">quinqueoculat</emphasis>
a as 
<taxonomicName box="[937,1061,189,212]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernovi">
<emphasis box="[937,1061,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">S. czernovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, despite their morphological and distributional differences. The main reason of these anomalies, is a reliance on insufficiently detailed descriptions. Resolution of this confused situation probably requires a revision of most species in the genus based on 
<typeStatus box="[1329,1388,261,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">types</typeStatus>
and fresh material from the type-localities.
</paragraph>
